# .shellcheckrc — repo-wide shellcheck configuration.
#
# Loaded automatically by shellcheck when invoked from the repo root.
# https://github.com/koalaman/shellcheck/blob/master/shellcheckrc
#
# Rationale per directive:
#
#   SC2317 — "Command appears to be unreachable". preflight.sh and
#            scripts/reproduce_dod.sh use `set -uo pipefail` WITHOUT `-e`
#            deliberately so each step's exit is captured by run_step()
#            / `if ... ; then ... else ...`. shellcheck can't see this
#            and flags every "unreachable" error branch.
#
#   SC2154 — "var is referenced but not assigned". preflight.sh and
#            scripts/reproduce_dod.sh read ${SKIP_*_SETUP} / ${SKIP_BUILD}
#            etc. which are environment-variable inputs (defaulted to "0"
#            further down). shellcheck can't trace env-var assignment.
#
#   SC2012 — "Use find instead of ls". tests/count_tests.sh and
#            tests/conformance/runner.sh use `ls tests/conformance/*.c`
#            to count version-controlled test fixtures. The names are
#            pinned (no whitespace, no newlines) so the warning is
#            theoretical; switching to `find ... -maxdepth 1` would
#            slow these 1-shot cosmetic counters without buying anything.
#
#   SC2015 — "A && B || C is not if-then-else". tests/conformance/runner.sh
#            uses `cargo test --release -- --list 2>&1 || true` to swallow
#            a missing-cargo path (SKIP_TEST_COUNT). The `|| true` makes
#            the &&/|| not actually be an if-then-else; shellcheck can't
#            trace that. Comment at the call site documents intent.
#
#   SC2016 — "Expressions don't expand in single quotes". scripts/preflight.sh
#            passes single-quoted shell snippets to `bash -c ...` for
#            run_step; the `$0`-style args inside those snippets are
#            intentionally literal at preflight-time (they expand inside
#            the sub-bash).
#
# `guest/build.sh` exports CC="$ZIG cc -target wasm32-freestanding -O2"
# at the top as a conventional overridable handle (build-script readers
# expect to be able to `CC=other-cc ./guest/build.sh`); shellcheck can't
# trace through Makefile-generated recipes at line 63. SC2034 is silenced
# only for that single declaration via an inline `# shellcheck disable=SC2034`
# next to the variable.

disable=SC2317,SC2154,SC2012,SC2015,SC2016